  "text": "Multilevel analyses were used to account for the nested structure of families within parent coaches, and parent coaches within training sites using hierarchical linear modeling software (HLM; [CITATION_1] . To capture parent behavior change across the 10 sessions, we calculated change scores for each family by subtracting the preintervention ratings of sensitivity from the postintervention ratings. Change scores were then entered into HLM equations that lacked any predictor variables to test whether the average expected change score (i.e., model intercept) was significantly different from 0. The tested model used the following form:",
